inputs.description: A collection of arguments for invoking getKafkaVersion.

preferredVersions.description: Ordered list of preferred Kafka versions. The first match in this list will be returned. Either `preferred_versions` or `version` must be set.

version.description: Version of MSK Kafka. For example 2.4.1.1 or "2.2.1" etc. Either `preferred_versions` or `version` must be set.

outputs.description: A collection of values returned by getKafkaVersion.

id.description: The provider-assigned unique ID for this managed resource.

status.description: Status of the MSK Kafka version eg. `ACTIVE` or `DEPRECATED`.
